text.tspan: An array of 512 electrodes was used to record from the retinal ganglion
cells of isolated macaque monkey retina while the retina was illuminated
with a moving bar at various speeds. Eyes were obtained from other
research groups when they concluded a monkey experiment.
Motion is an important signal for the visual system to represent, and this
signal starts in the retinal ganglion cells.
